title: Lions sign Fluellen, put Walker on IR
text:
Lions sign Fluellen, put Walker on IR AP 
Oct 7, 2015 at 10:52p ET + Updated Oct 7, 2015 at 10:52p ET 
ALLEN PARK, Mich. (AP) -- The Detroit Lions have signed defensive tackle Andre Fluellen and put defensive tackle Tyrunn Walker on injured reserve. 
Walker is out for the season because of a dislocated ankle and broken leg, and the Lions confirmed Wednesday they have signed Fluellen. 
The 30-year-old Fluellen has played off and on for the Lions since they drafted him in the third round in 2008. He's played 75 games for Detroit, including eight last season.
